# Migration — the 7 Rs

Every workload is being one of these:

| R | Means | When |
|---|---|---|
| **Retire** | turn off | unused / duplicated |
| **Retain** | leave on-prem | latency / compliance / lock-in |
| **Rehost** | lift-and-shift → EC2 | fastest, *"forklift"* |
| **Relocate** | VMware → VMware Cloud on AWS | the VMware path |
| **Replatform** | lift-and-tinker (DB → RDS) | modest gains, no rewrite |
| **Repurchase** | → SaaS (buy Salesforce) | SaaS equiv exists |
| **Refactor** | rebuild cloud-native | highest value + effort |

## Sequencing

**Retire + Retain first** (cut scope) → **Rehost the majority** (get out fast) → **Replatform + Refactor over time**.

Refactoring everything up front → **miss the deadline**. Cloud first, modernise there.
